##The doctor from "best photo of the day. " We found him

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

Li Jiawei is a reporter for the paper

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Official microblog of Zhongshan Hospital affiliated to Fudan University, Shanghai

On March 5, Dr. Liu Kai, a member of the Hubei medical team from the Sun Yat Sen hospital affiliated with Fudan University in Shanghai, stopped while escorting a patient for a CT scan, the 87-year-old man, who has been in hospital for nearly a month, was treated to a sunset he hasn't seen in a long time.

Two figures, a patient and a doctor in the setting sun, were voted the best photo of the day after the heartwarming moment was captured and touched by countless netizens.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
That evening, Dr. Liu Kai, 27, returned to his room after a busy day and spoke by phone with the _ paper _, describing how he and Mr. Chen happened to enjoy the sunset in the early evening.

The 87-year-old was admitted to the hospital as a critically ill patient and has been recovering under the care of a Shanghai medical team. Just after 4 p.m. today, Liu Kai wheeled him to a follow up CT scan, and on his way back to the ward, the sun was shining brightly on the patient and the doctor.

"I think the old gentleman is quite happy, ask him to want to see (the setting Sun) , he said yes. " Then two people stop.

For the old man, Liu Kai said, he hadn't seen sunlight in a month. In fact, for himself, every day out early and late, has been staying in the ward, and rarely see the sun. So when two people see the sun bathing in the sunset, actually quite happy.

"What do you think? " Liu Kai asked the old gentleman after he had stopped, and the latter replied, "the sunset is fine. "

After three or four minutes, Liu Kai knew that the old man's condition was not stable and the temperature outside was not high, so he pushed him back to the ward. Liu Kai said the old man was in a good mood and went to bed soon.

Dr. Liu Kai was part of the fourth team of Hubei Medical team from Zhongshan Hospital, which has been fighting on the Wuhan Front since Feb. 7.

When the Shanghai medical team first arrived, the old man was very ill and ignored everyone. The old man's family lived far away, traffic in Wuhan City stopped, the family to deliver things is not easy, Zhongshan Hospital medical team will contract all the life care.

CAKES, fruit, all kinds of daily necessities, nutrition, are sent to the old man and other patients. After more than 20 days, the old man not only got better and better, but also got on well with the medical staff.

The medical team of Zhongshan Hospital is in charge of the 20 and 22 wards of the East Hospital of Wuhan University People's Hospital. "The vast majority of patients are now stable and some have been discharged, " Liu Kai said.

When a critically ill patient, who had recently been discharged from the hospital with a mild illness, wrote down the names of all the medical staff on a piece of paper. Many patients leave the hospital to tell the Shanghai medical staff: When the epidemic has passed, please eat hot and dry noodles.
